# Lock SQL migration bodies to LF on commit + checkout.
#
# The 66 reconciled migrations in scripts/.116/manifest.json carry an
# integrity contract: md5(file_bytes) must equal the production md5 of
# array_to_string(statements,'') from supabase_migrations.schema_migrations.
# Production stores LF. A CRLF normalisation on checkout would break the
# contract silently.
#
# This rule preempts that by pinning *.sql to LF regardless of the user's
# core.autocrlf setting. Re-verify the rollup after any .sql edit with:
#   node scripts/.116/rollup-fingerprint.mjs
*.sql text eol=lf

# Lock the full-graph attestation reference files to LF on both index and
# working tree. The harness loads them via readFileSync + .split('\n');
# a stray \r on Windows checkouts would silently shatter every line and
# break the immune fingerprint. CI runs on Linux so this only affects
# local validation, but pinning eliminates the surprise.
scripts/.116c/prod-*.txt text eol=lf
scripts/.116c/rebuild-*.txt text eol=lf
